"{\"uid\": \"myrepublica.nagariknetwork.com-news-olympian-hamal-releases-autobiography\", \"text\": \"Subscribe Now  KATHMANDU, Sept 20: Olympian Surendra Bahadaur Hamal has launched his autobiography \\\"Olympian\\\" at National Sports Council, Tripureshwor in the Capital City on Tuesday.  The book\\u00a0was jointly lauched\\u00a0by the Olympians\\u00a0-\\u00a0Anita Maharjan (Shooting), Pushpa Ojha (Athletics), Sangina Baidhya (Taekwondo), Jangdish Pradhan (Weightlifting) and Hamal himself.  \\\"Olympian\\\"-the first autobiography of a Nepali\\u00a0sportsmen, is an inspirational book especially for aspiring Nepali players. In the book, Hamal, as a storyteller, has beautifully shared his passionate sports journey along with the challenges he had encountered while achieving his dreams.  During the function, Hamal shared his short life stories that he had missed in the book.Various members of the Olympic Committee also accompanied the session.  Including various national sports events, Hamal has also represented Nepal in South Asian Games (SAG), Olympics\\u00a0and other international sports events in the weightlifting category.  Hamal is also Nepal's first weightlifting medalist.  Ballot Box Revolt: What RSP's breakthrough victory...  Warning, Threat or Opportunity? Nepal's major part...  Granary in crisis: Water politics leave Madhesh pa...  \\\"China stands ready to work with Nepal to carry forward the traditional friendship, deepen practical cooperation and advance bilateral relations\\\", read the statement.  Building Nepal's Digital Future  Fuel shortages in Nepal: A hidden threat to health a...  Second Innings of Balen and Gagan  Who will become Balen's climate pilot?  Three \\\"S\\\" factors-sulabhata (availability), sangat (peer influence), and siko (imitation)-are driving Madhesh's youth toward drug addiction.<...  Three \\\"S\\\" factors-sulabhata (availability), sangat (peer influence), and siko (imitation)-are driving Madhesh's youth toward drug addiction